Program: Great Lives
Title: Beatrix Potter
Link: https://www.bbc.co.uk/programmes/p00glwmb
Last Broadcast Date: Fri 18 Nov 2005
Fiona Reynolds, Director-General of the National Trust, argues in favour of the greatness of Beatrix Potter. But does her greatness lie in her literary achievements or in her skills as a conservationist? Francine Stock presents.